This follows the same principles and plan as in the first introductory moduleObjectives/eesmärkid:  In this second module, the introductory steps of the 1st module are expanded upon. There is a continuing overview of clinical nutrition, the basic science underlying the patient's requirements and how to implement these needs.  The student is taught about the effects of age and obesity and more thoroughly about the substrates used in artificial nutrition.  The student is introduced to the importance of teamwork and ethical practice in clinical nutrition.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student completing the module: * knows effects of age on nutritional needs * knows generally about obesity * knows about the substrates and methods for enteral tube feeding * knows about substrates and techniques for parenteral nutrition  * knows the relationships between physical activity and diet * knows and values teamwork * understands the ethics of nutrition
